76561198049432668,Recommended,227580,19061180,"Posted: 13 November, 2015",all,Burgie,"Introduction10,000,000 is an hybrid RPG/Action/Puzzle game. Steady progress in the game allows you to gain the tools to break out of your prison.Title:10,000,000Genre:Action, Casual, Indie, RPGDeveloper:EightyEightGamesPublisher: EightyEightGamesRelease Date: 15 Jan, 2013Main ReviewIt's not an easy game, but it's addictive in how it works. Your character progresses in a dungeon and you match blocks together in order to keep on moving, matching keys to open a door or chest, swords or shields to fight. The game is a race against time. It's quite fast paced and easy to get into, though hard to keep going and finish it. The RNG can sometimes really screw you up - and you may need to reset a level just because you didn't get what you needed for a long time. It's satisfying to see the big numbers appear, and each shake of the screen when you match blocks is pretty cool.You need to reach the score 10,000,000 in order to complete the game, and all the runs beforehand allow you to buy upgrades such as potions, weapons, gear, score accumulators in order to improve your score further, get better upgrades - until you're good enough to hit the top score to beat the game.You can collect four items that stay with you even when a run fails, to make future runs easier. It can get really fraustrating, since even if you have every single upgrade, getting the final score is still difficult. However that also makes it fun! The music also helps a lot to get you more stressed.Visually the game at times make it hard to see what's going on, especially when managing your position in the game. The character screen is small. On the left of the main ""running"" screen is a skull, on the right is a finish line and a smily face. If your character is at the right of the screen, it's harder to counter a threat since you don't see it until it's already on you. If your character is on the left of the screen, you'll die a lot faster if you don't get the block combination you need to open a door, since your run ends if the skull catches up with you.Pros and ConsPro'sAddictiveChallenging/Fast pacedGood musicFun system to work withConsAddictiveChallenging/Fast PacedMUSIC MAKES YOU STRESSEDRNG hates youThe screen doesn't moveTL'DROverall VerdictI recommend this game to other people. I think it's worth a playthrough, and at this price, it's nothing to complain about. Be prepared to get very addicted ... and possibly shout a bit at the screen.Want moar?Click here to join my steam groupandClick here to follow my curator page!"
