,Recommended,227580,265274,"Posted: 21 March, 2013",all,Kittenpox,"If you're fond of Bejewelled (or similar games) and games with RPG elements, this may be for you. The video gives a basic rundown of the gameplay - slide rows and columns to make matches of 3 or more of the same item, and your character will use it to attack with sword and staff, open locked chests and doors, etc.I finished this in a little over 6 hours, but it was thoroughly enjoyable. (Then again, I have played quite a bit of Bejewelled Blitz so I was already fond of the control system - the hardest part was adapting to sliding rows/columns rather than swapping individual adjacent tiles.)If you're looking for a casual game with an RPG feel, I certainly recommend '10,000,000'."
