76561198015202396,Recommended,227580,14354540,"Posted: 6 February, 2015",all,Mirisio,"This game is very simple, it's your average 3 tiles match game but with some more depth. You got ressources tiles, Woods and Stones, which let's you gain ressources for upgrading your shops. You got keys which let's you open chests and doors. You got bags which will give you a item from time to time. You got attack tiles, Sword and Staff, which make you attack the enemies in front of you and depending of the enemies you're fighting it might be better to use physical attacks (Sword) or magical one (Staff). Shield tiles let you absorb a damage from the enemies. There's also a star tiles which basically can match with any other tiles.With the shop you can upgrade your gears, like your swords so you do more physical damage with sword tiles. You can upgrade your armor so enemies take more time to attack you. You gain experiences so you can unlock skills, like more chances for your magical attacks to make a abnormal status to the enemies. There's also potions that will handicap you so you can gain more points for exemple.The graphics are simple but got charms, the really big selling point to me is the music which is fantastic in this game. So if you like 3 match tiles like I do, this is definetly worth a buy."
