,Recommended,227580,14240243,"Posted: 30 January, 2015",all,みoƦƦoƦ ₣o父,"Hey everyone and this is my review about the game!This is a Fast paced Puzzle game.Interface/Menu/SettingsThere is NO Menu.But there is a music slidebar available.There is also a sound slidebar available.There fullscreen and windowed mode available.No resolution sizes available.You are able to delete your save file and start from the bottom again.About the game.During the puzzle you have to swap the tile things and make a match together. 3x or more of the same tile at least. Each matching tile is having a different outcome. Sword and staves will damage the enemy. Keys are unlocking chests and doors. Wood and ores are needed to unlock new things at the hub. Shield is needed to reduce damage and make the run longer and the chest has a chance of giving you an item. Your end goal is to reach 10M in one RUN. You do have to upgrade yourself to make a run last longer. Once you have read the left side, your game will be over!Unlocking new things.Very easy game to understand.Repetitive but addictive.You can upgrade yourself by making your runs a little bit easier.Very interesting game!Could be short if you are doing really well.The 8 bit music is very well done! Including in Combat puzzle mode!There are challenges that you should be able to complete for rewards.Other things.If you are familiar with the game ""tetris attack"" on the Snes or ""Pokemon puzzle league"" on the N64. This game plays almost the same.-------------------I Give this game a 9/10"
