,Recommended,227580,5065533,"Posted: 7 March, 2013",all,Kadzie,"This game... hmm... it's difficult to describe, but the gameplay is a fairly unique mix of RPG/Dungeon Crawling along with tile-matching games. It's a great game to kill a few minutes (hours) on, and all you need to do is make a cup of tea (Or whatever's your poison) and play the mouse-only game whilst sipping ones favourite beverage.Don't be put off by the simple graphics and simple gameplay, it's a game well worth the few £'s it's up for :)"
,Recommended,227580,15384466,"Posted: 15 April, 2015",all,Tanya,"This one is a 50/50.It's a simple, fast-paced match 3 game where you make matches based on the event presented to you. i.e. if your character comes to a chest, you match key icons to unlock it and move on. The longer you stand behind an obstacle without clearing it, you are pushed back until you eventually 'lose'.While playing you can match resource tiles which allow you to upgrade things on your ship, which pretty much just increases your damage, or defense, or something else that will allow you to travel further next time you adventure.The main problem with the game is that there is an artificial level of difficulty. You adventure for a certain amount of time, then you will inevitably reach a monster much harder than the previous ones which acts as a barrier to your progress until you unlock enough upgrades to move on. In other words, it doesn't really matter how well you play the game, you won't be able to go as far as you 'can'.Nevertheless I still kept coming to play it just because the main part of the game is very addictive."
